
@startuml

' Define classes
class Doctor {
    +String fullName
    +String address
    +String phoneNumber
    +int practitionerNumber
    +Image signature
    +Date validFrom
}

class Patient {
    +String firstName
    +String lastName
    +Date dateOfBirth
    +String address
    +String phoneNumber
    +String healthNumber
}

class Requisition {
    +Doctor doctor
    +Patient patient
    +Date issuedDate
    +TestGroup testGroup
    +List<Test> tests
    +RepeatSchedule repeatSchedule
}

class Test {
    +String name
    +Duration duration
    +boolean requiresAppointment
    +TestGroup testGroup
    +Result result
    +Report report
}

class TestGroup {
    +String groupName
}

class RepeatSchedule {
    +int repetitions
    +Interval interval
}

enum Interval {
    WEEKLY
    MONTHLY
    HALF_YEARLY
    YEARLY
}

class Appointment {
    +Requisition requisition
    +Lab lab
    +Date date
    +Time startTime
    +Time endTime
    +String confirmationNumber
    +double cancellationFee
}

class Lab {
    +String name
    +String address
    +String registrationNumber
    +Time startBusinessHour
    +Time endBusinessHour
    +Map<Date, List<TimeSlot>> timeSlots
}

class Result {
    +String outcome (e.g., "Positive", "Negative")
}

class Report {
    +String content
}

class Duration {
    +int minutes
}

class TimeSlot {
    +Time startTime
    +Time endTime
}

' Associations
Doctor --> Requisition : issues
Patient --> Requisition : isSubjectOf
Requisition --> TestGroup : belongsTo
TestGroup --> Test : contains
Test --> TestGroup : inGroup
Requisition --> RepeatSchedule : has
Requisition --> Appointment : mayHave
Appointment --> Lab : at
Lab --> Appointment : offers
Test --> Result : has
Test --> Report : has
Lab --> TimeSlot : provides

' Constraints
note right of Doctor
    A doctor cannot prescribe a test for themselves.
end note

note right of Test
    Some tests can be grouped together if they are in the same TestGroup.
end note

note right of Appointment
    Patients can only book one appointment at a time for repeated tests.
    Changes within 24 hours incur a fee.
end note

@enduml

---

### ✅ Key Features Captured:

- **Doctor**: Issues requisitions with required information including digital signature and practitioner number.
- **Patient**: Has personal info and health number; uses requisition to make appointments.
- **Requisition**: Links doctor and patient; includes a group of tests from the same category.
- **TestGroup**: Ensures only compatible tests are grouped together.
- **Test**: Can have duration, result, and report. May require an appointment or not.
- **RepeatSchedule**: Defines repetition rules for tests.
- **Appointment**: Booked by patients; tied to a specific lab and time slot.
- **Lab**: Provides tests and has fixed business hours; charges for late cancellations.
- **Result & Report**: Attached to each test.
- **TimeSlot**: Used for managing available appointment slots.

